 power and powerless¡ness, self-determination and cultural control, violence and pleasure. Pleasures and Perils illuminates the methodological and ethical issues anthropologists face when they conduct research on sex, especially among girls. The sexually explicit narratives conveyed in this book challenge not only the reader's own thoughts on sexuality but also the broader limits and possibilities of ethnography.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aGirlsxAttitudesxSaint Kitts and NevisxNevis. 0aGirlsxSexual behaviorxSaint Kitts and NevisxNevis. 0aGirlsxSexual behaviorzSaint Kitts and NeviszNevis. 0aGirlszSaint Kitts and NeviszNevisxAttitudes. 0aSex in popular culturexSaint Kitts and NevisxNevis. 0aSex in popular culturezSaint Kitts and NeviszNevis. 0aSexxSocial aspectsxSaint Kitts and NevisxNevis. 0aSexxSocial aspectszSaint Kitts and NeviszNevis. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066331040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813546964423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813546964.jpg  a978-3-11-066331-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-068861-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK